WEBVTT

00:00:00.050 --> 00:00:01.750
Hello and welcome back.

00:00:02.470 --> 00:00:07.610
In this lesson, I will show you how to switch models between OpenAI and DeepSeek.

00:00:08.050 --> 00:00:10.810
But you could switch to other models too if you like.

00:00:11.490 --> 00:00:15.270
However, for demonstration purposes, I will use DeepSeek.

00:00:15.710 --> 00:00:19.170
Head over to the DeepSeek website and sign up for an account.

00:00:19.790 --> 00:00:22.350
If you see Chinese text, you can switch to English.

00:00:24.790 --> 00:00:28.190
After logging in, click on Access API.

00:00:31.120 --> 00:00:32.220
Top up some money.

00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:36.300
You could use PayPal or credit card.

00:00:37.380 --> 00:00:40.060
Then, create new API key.

00:00:42.600 --> 00:00:45.500
Once it is created, copy it to a file.

00:00:47.220 --> 00:00:50.300
If you forgot the key, you won't be able to view it again.

00:00:51.260 --> 00:00:55.180
In that case, just delete the old key and create a new one.

00:00:56.600 --> 00:00:58.400
There is no extra charge.

00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:02.020
Then, we open a command prompt.

00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:08.090
List the existing modules using this command

00:01:08.090 --> 00:01:13.080
You will see that there is only one model configured

00:01:13.080 --> 00:01:16.540
which is OpenAI GPT 5.4

00:01:16.540 --> 00:01:18.880
and it is listed as the default

00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:28.040
To add another model, we run this command

00:01:28.040 --> 00:01:29.900
OpenClaw Onboard

00:01:29.900 --> 00:01:33.380
Use arrow keys to select Yes

00:01:33.380 --> 00:01:37.150
Select Manual

00:01:37.150 --> 00:01:45.250
Select Update Values

00:01:45.250 --> 00:01:50.160
Select Local Gateway

00:01:50.160 --> 00:01:53.900
Do not change the workspace directory

00:01:53.900 --> 00:01:57.460
Scroll down to DeepSeek

00:01:57.460 --> 00:02:03.970
Paste in the API key

00:02:03.970 --> 00:02:07.500
Select Keep Current

00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:12.010
Accept the default gateway port

00:02:12.010 --> 00:02:14.290
Select Loopback

00:02:14.290 --> 00:02:16.050
Select Token

00:02:16.050 --> 00:02:17.910
Select Off

00:02:17.910 --> 00:02:21.690
Press Enter for generate Plaintext token

00:02:21.690 --> 00:02:25.170
Use arrow button to select No

00:02:25.170 --> 00:02:31.290
We already have telegram configured previously and do not wish to add another channel.

00:02:31.290 --> 00:02:35.710
Select skip for now.

00:02:35.710 --> 00:02:42.550
For skills, select no.

00:02:42.550 --> 00:02:50.380
Press spacebar to select skip for now.

00:02:50.380 --> 00:02:53.980
Again press spacebar to select skip for now.

00:02:53.980 --> 00:02:57.920
Again select yes.

00:02:57.920 --> 00:03:00.940
Just press enter.

00:03:00.940 --> 00:03:03.260
Select restart.

00:03:03.260 --> 00:03:10.280
Press enter yes.

00:03:10.280 --> 00:03:15.690
Clear screen using command cls.

00:03:15.690 --> 00:03:32.820
To open web UI, type in command, open claw dashboard, type in hello. It replies. Ask

00:03:32.820 --> 00:03:44.810
it what model are you on, it replies saying it is on deep seek. So it works.

00:03:44.810 --> 00:04:05.260
Go to telegram, clear history, start a new session, ask it the same question, and it

00:04:05.260 --> 00:04:09.120
also confirms it is on deep seek.

00:04:09.120 --> 00:04:16.580
In the terminal, clear the screen, then type in command, open claw models list.

00:04:16.580 --> 00:04:27.640
You can see deep seek is the default, but GPT is still there.

00:04:27.640 --> 00:04:31.500
Let's set it to GPT.

00:04:31.500 --> 00:04:35.240
Use the command, open claw models set.

00:04:35.240 --> 00:04:45.000
Highlight the model you want to set, and right click to copy it.

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:50.960
It confirms changing the default model to GPT 5.4.

00:04:50.960 --> 00:04:54.380
We need to restart the gateway.

00:04:54.380 --> 00:04:58.820
Use this command, openclaw gateway restart.

00:04:58.820 --> 00:05:10.620
After restarting, ask it what model are you on, and it confirms it is on GPT 5.4.

00:05:10.620 --> 00:05:20.390
In the terminal, we clear the screen, then list the models again.

00:05:20.390 --> 00:05:26.390
Now, it shows the default model has been changed to GPT 5.4.

00:05:26.390 --> 00:05:29.270
But DeepSeek is still there.

00:05:29.270 --> 00:05:32.390
Let's change it back to DeepSeek.

00:05:32.390 --> 00:05:35.090
Use the same command we used previously,

00:05:35.090 --> 00:05:38.770
openclaw Model Set, select the DeepSeek full name,

00:05:38.770 --> 00:05:40.630 
and right-click to copy.

00:05:40.630 --> 00:05:42.550
Paste it in.

00:05:42.550 --> 00:05:46.670
It confirms changing the default model to DeepSeek.

00:05:46.670 --> 00:05:50.290
Now, let's restart the gateway.

00:05:50.290 --> 00:06:00.190
After restarting, we ask it, what model are you on?

00:06:00.190 --> 00:06:06.090
If it still says GPT, we need to refresh the web UI.

00:06:06.090 --> 00:06:11.800
Click on the Refresh button.

00:06:11.800 --> 00:06:15.740
Then repeat the question.

00:06:15.740 --> 00:06:18.950
Ask it to check again.

00:06:18.950 --> 00:06:24.540
And now it confirms it is back on DeepSeek.

00:06:24.540 --> 00:06:27.980
In the terminal, we clear the screen

00:06:27.980 --> 00:06:32.220
and list the models again.

00:06:32.220 --> 00:06:35.760
We see that the default model is now DeepSeek.

00:06:36.540 --> 00:06:42.540
So this is how we can add another model and also how to easily switch models.

00:06:42.540 --> 00:06:46.540
The same technique applies to other models as well.

00:06:46.540 --> 00:06:48.540
That is all for this video.

00:06:48.540 --> 00:06:50.540
Thanks for watching.

